PVP.description: Players can hurt and kill other players

PauseEmpty.description: Game time stops when there are no players online

GlobalChat.description: Toggles global chat on or off.

Open.description: Clients may join without already having an account in the whitelist. If set to false, administrators must manually create username/password combos.

ServerWelcomeMessage.description: The first welcome message visible in the chat panel. This will be displayed immediately after player login. you can use RGB colours to chance the colour of the welcome message. You can also use <LINE> to create a separate lines within your text. Use: <RGB:1,0,0> This message will show up red!
ServerWelcomeMessage.value: Welcome to Solid Content Project Zomboid Server! <LINE> <LINE> To interact with the Chat panel: press Tab, T, or Enter. <LINE> <LINE> The Tab key will change the target stream of the message. <LINE> <LINE> Global Streams: /all <LINE> Local Streams: /say, /yell <LINE> Special Streams: /whisper, /safehouse, /faction, /all. <LINE> <LINE> Press the Up arrow to cycle through your message history. Click the Gear icon to customize chat. <LINE> <LINE> Happy surviving!

AutoCreateUserInWhiteList.description: Add unknown usernames to the whitelist when players join. Clients will supply their own username/password on joining. (This is for Open=true servers)

DisplayUserName.description: Display usernames above player's heads in-game.

ShowFirstAndLastName.description: Display first & last name above player's heads.

SpawnPoint.description: Force every new player to spawn at these set x,y,z world coordinates. Find desired coordinates at map.projectzomboid.com. (Ignored when 0,0,0)

SafetySystem.description: Players can enter and leave PVP on an individual basis. A player can only hurt another player when at least one of them is in PVP mode - as shown by the unobscured skull and crossbones on the left of the screen. When SafetySystem=false, players are free to hurt each other at any time if PVP is enabled.

ShowSafety.description: Display a skull icon over the head of players who have entered PVP mode

SafetyToggleTimer.description: The time it takes for a player to enter and leave PVP mode\nMinimum=0 Maximum=1000 Default=2

SafetyCooldownTimer.description: The delay before a player can enter or leave PVP mode again, having recently done so\nMinimum=0 Maximum=1000 Default=3

SpawnItems.description: Item types new players spawn with.\nSeparate multiple item types with commas.\nExample: Base.Axe,Base.Bag_BigHikingBag

DefaultPort.description: Default starting port for player data. If UDP, this is this one of two ports used.\nMinimum=0 Maximum=65535 Default=16261

ResetID.description: Reset ID determines if the server has undergone a soft-reset. If this number does match the client, the client must create a new character. Used in conjunction with PlayerServerID. It is strongly advised that you backup these IDs somewhere\nMinimum=0 Maximum=2147483647 Default=847748113

Mods.description: Enter the mod loading ID here. It can be found in \Steam\steamapps\workshop\modID\mods\modName\info.txt

Map.description: Enter the foldername of the mod found in \Steam\steamapps\workshop\modID\mods\modName\media\maps\

DoLuaChecksum.description: Kick clients whose game files don't match the server's.

Public.description: Shows the server on the in-game browser. (Note: Steam-enabled servers are always visible in the Steam server browser)

PublicName.description: Name of the server displayed in the in-game browser and, if applicable, the Steam browser

PublicDescription.description: Description displayed in the in-game public server browser. Typing \n will create a new line in your description
PublicDescription.value:
Check Out For A Good Time: Solid Content YouTube Let's Play Streamer!
https://youtube.com/solidcontent
Discord Chat: https://discord.gg/WfRvcQkuxN
MrKeon Public Gaming Server Hosting
Email me at mrkeon.com@gmail.com to request web hosting for you.

MaxPlayers.description:
Maximum number of players that can be on the server at one time. This excludes admins.
WARNING: Server player counts above 32 will potentially result in poor map streaming and desync. Please advance with caution.\nMinimum=1 Maximum=100 Default=32

PingLimit.description: Ping limit, in milliseconds, before a player is kicked from the server. (Set to 100 to disable)\nMinimum=100 Maximum=2147483647 Default=400

HoursForLootRespawn.description: After X hours, all containers in the world will respawn loot. To spawn loot a container must have been looted at least once. Loot respawn is not impacted by visibility or subsequent looting.\nMinimum=0 Maximum=2147483647 Default=0

MaxItemsForLootRespawn.description: Containers with a number of items greater, or equal to, this setting will not respawn\nMinimum=1 Maximum=2147483647 Default=4

ConstructionPreventsLootRespawn.description: Items will not respawn in buildings that players have barricaded or built in

DropOffWhiteListAfterDeath.description: Remove player accounts from the whitelist after death. This prevents players creating a new character after death on Open=false servers

NoFire.description: All forms of fire are disabled - except for campfires

AnnounceDeath.description: If checked, every time a player dies a global message will be displayed in the chat

MinutesPerPage.description: The number of in-game minutes it takes to read one page of a book\nMinimum=0.00 Maximum=60.00 Default=1.00

SaveWorldEveryMinutes.description: Loaded parts of the map are saved after this set number of real-world minutes have passed. (The map is usually saved only after clients leave a loaded area)\nMinimum=0 Maximum=2147483647 Default=0

PlayerSafehouse.description: Both admins and players can claim safehouses

SafehouseAllowTrepass.description: Allow non-members to enter a safehouse without being invited

SafehouseAllowLoot.description: Allow non-members to take items from safehouses

SafehouseAllowRespawn.description: Players will respawn in a safehouse that they were a member of before they died

SafehouseDaySurvivedToClaim.description: Players must have survived this number of in-game days before they are allowed to claim a safehouse\nMinimum=0 Maximum=2147483647 Default=0

SafeHouseRemovalTime.description: Players are automatically removed from a safehouse they have not visited for this many real-world hours\nMinimum=0 Maximum=2147483647 Default=144

SafehouseAllowNonResidential.description: Governs whether players can claim non-residential buildings.

AllowDestructionBySledgehammer.description: Allow players to destroy world objects with sledgehammers

SledgehammerOnlyInSafehouse.description: Allow players to destroy world objects only in their safehouse (require AllowDestructionBySledgehammer to true).

KickFastPlayers.description: Kick players that appear to be moving faster than is possible. May be buggy -- use with caution.

ServerPlayerID.description: ServerPlayerID determines if a character is from another server, or single player. This value may be changed by soft resets. If this number does match the client, the client must create a new character. This is used in conjunction with ResetID. It is strongly advised that you backup these IDs somewhere

RCONPort.description: The port for the RCON (Remote Console)\nMinimum=0 Maximum=65535 Default=27015

DiscordEnable.description: Enables global text chat integration with a Discord channel

DiscordChannel.description: The Discord channel name. (Try the separate channel ID option if having difficulties)

DiscordChannelID.description: The Discord channel ID. (Use if having difficulties with Discord channel name option)

Password.description: Clients must know this password to join the server. (Ignored when hosting a server via the Host button)

MaxAccountsPerUser.description: Limits the number of different accounts a single Steam user may create on this server. Ignored when using the Hosts button.\nMinimum=0 Maximum=2147483647 Default=0

SleepAllowed.description: Players are allowed to sleep when their survivor becomes tired, but they do not NEED to sleep

SleepNeeded.description: Players get tired and need to sleep. (Ignored if SleepAllowed=false)

WorkshopItems.description: List Workshop Mod IDs for the server to download. Each must be separated by a semicolon. Example: WorkshopItems=514427485;513111049

SteamScoreboard.description: Show Steam usernames and avatars in the Players list. Can be true (visible to everyone), false (visible to no one), or admin (visible to only admins)

UPnP.description: Attempt to configure a UPnP-enabled internet gateway to automatically setup port forwarding rules. The server will fall back to default ports if this fails

VoiceMinDistance.description: The minimum tile distance over which VOIP sounds can be heard.\nMinimum=0.00 Maximum=100000.00 Default=10.00

VoiceMaxDistance.description: The maximum tile distance over which VOIP sounds can be heard.\nMinimum=0.00 Maximum=100000.00 Default=100.00

server_browser_announced_ip.description: Set the IP from which the server is broadcast. This is for network configurations with multiple IP addresses, such as server farms

PlayerRespawnWithSelf.description: Players can respawn in-game at the coordinates where they died

PlayerRespawnWithOther.description: Players can respawn in-game at a split screen / Remote Play player's location

FastForwardMultiplier.description: Governs how fast time passes while players sleep. Value multiplies the speed of the time that passes during sleeping.\nMinimum=1.00 Maximum=100.00 Default=40.00

DisableSafehouseWhenPlayerConnected.description: Safehouse acts like a normal house if a member of the safehouse is connected (so secure when players are offline)

Faction.description: Players can create factions when true

FactionDaySurvivedToCreate.description: Players must survive this number of in-game days before being allowed to create a faction\nMinimum=0 Maximum=2147483647 Default=0

FactionPlayersRequiredForTag.description: Number of players required as faction members before the faction owner can create a group tag\nMinimum=1 Maximum=2147483647 Default=1

DisableRadioStaff.description: Disables radio transmissions from players with an access level

DisableRadioAdmin.description: Disables radio transmissions from players with 'admin' access level

DisableRadioGM.description: Disables radio transmissions from players with 'gm' access level

DisableRadioOverseer.description: Disables radio transmissions from players with 'overseer' access level

DisableRadioModerator.description: Disables radio transmissions from players with 'moderator' access level

DisableRadioInvisible.description: Disables radio transmissions from invisible players

ClientCommandFilter.description: Semicolon-separated list of commands that will not be written to the cmd.txt server log. For example: \n-vehicle. Inputting * means do NOT write any vehicle command. Inputting: \n+vehicle.installPart means DO write that command

ClientActionLogs.description: Semicolon-separated list of actions that will be written to the ClientActionLogs.txt server log.

PerkLogs.description: Track changes in player perk levels in PerkLog.txt server log

ItemNumbersLimitPerContainer.description: Maximum number of items that can be placed in a container.  Zero means there is no limit. (PLEASE NOTE: This includes individual small items such as nails. A limit of 50 will mean only 50 nails can be stored.)\nMinimum=0 Maximum=9000 Default=0

BloodSplatLifespanDays.description:
Number of days before old blood splats are removed.
Removal happens when map chunks are loaded.
Zero means they will never disappear\nMinimum=0 Maximum=365 Default=0

AllowNonAsciiUsername.description: Allow use of non-ASCII (cyrillic etc) characters in usernames

RemovePlayerCorpsesOnCorpseRemoval.description: If enabled, when HoursForCorpseRemoval triggers, it will also remove player?s corpses from the ground.

TrashDeleteAll.description: If true, player can use the "delete all" button on bins.

PVPMeleeWhileHitReaction.description: If true, player can hit again when struck by another player.

MouseOverToSeeDisplayName.description: If true, players will have to mouse over someone to see their display name.

HidePlayersBehindYou.description: If true, automatically hide the player you can't see (like zombies).

PVPMeleeDamageModifier.description: Damage multiplier for PVP melee attacks.\nMinimum=0.00 Maximum=500.00 Default=30.00

PVPFirearmDamageModifier.description: Damage multiplier for PVP ranged attacks.\nMinimum=0.00 Maximum=500.00 Default=50.00

CarEngineAttractionModifier.description: Modify the range of zombie attraction to cars. (Lower values can help with lag.)\nMinimum=0.00 Maximum=10.00 Default=0.50

PlayerBumpPlayer.description: Governs whether players bump (and knock over) other players when running through them.

MapRemotePlayerVisibility.description: Controls display of remote players on the in-game map.\n1=Hidden 2=Friends 3=Everyone\nMinimum=1 Maximum=3 Default=1

AntiCheatProtectionType2ThresholdMultipl.description: Threshold value multiplier for anti-cheat protection: type 2.\nMinimum=1.00 Maximum=10.00 Default=3.00

AntiCheatProtectionType3ThresholdMultipl.description: Threshold value multiplier for anti-cheat protection: type 3.\nMinimum=1.00 Maximum=10.00 Default=1.00

AntiCheatProtectionType4ThresholdMultipl.description: Threshold value multiplier for anti-cheat protection: type 4.\nMinimum=1.00 Maximum=10.00 Default=1.00

AntiCheatProtectionType9ThresholdMultipl.description: Threshold value multiplier for anti-cheat protection: type 9.\nMinimum=1.00 Maximum=10.00 Default=1.00

AntiCheatProtectionType15ThresholdMultip.description: Threshold value multiplier for anti-cheat protection: type 15.\nMinimum=1.00 Maximum=10.00 Default=1.00

AntiCheatProtectionType20ThresholdMultip.description: Threshold value multiplier for anti-cheat protection: type 20.\nMinimum=1.00 Maximum=10.00 Default=1.00
